  "prompt": "Can you see someone's status message if they block you on WhatsApp?",
  "response": "No, if someone has blocked you on WhatsApp, you will not be able to see their status messages. When a user blocks you on WhatsApp, several restrictions are put in place to maintain their privacy. Specifically:\n\n1. **Profile Information**: You won't be able to see their profile photo, \"Last Seen,\" or \"Online\" status.\n2. **Status Updates**: Their status messages (similar to stories on other social platforms) will be hidden from you.\n3. **Messages**: Any messages you send to them will not be delivered, and you won't receive any messages from them.\n4. **Calls**: You won't be able to call them or see their WhatsApp voice and video call activity.\n\nBlocking is designed to prevent any form of interaction or visibility between the blocker and the blocked person. If you suspect you've been blocked and want to confirm, aside from not seeing their status messages, you may also notice that you can't see their profile photo updates or send them messages that reach delivery (indicated by a single check mark).\n\n**Note:** These features are in place to protect users' privacy and ensure a safe communication environment. If you believe you've been mistakenly blocked, the best course of action is to reach out to the person through alternative means or respect their decision.",
